enhanced_by.reason: The generateValid method relies on the birthday method to determine the birth date, which is a critical part of the ID number generation.
The generateValid method relies on the gender method to determine the gender, which is also a critical part of the ID number generation.
Both generateValid and generateInvalid methods generate ID numbers but with different validity. Comparing the outputs of these methods can help in constructing assertions for edge cases.
The checksum method is used to calculate the control digit for the ID number. Assertions can be enhanced by verifying the checksum calculation against the generated ID number.
